<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>31-4417</num>
  <heading>Mutual companies — Requirements before doing business.</heading>
  <text>No domestic mutual company shall transact any business until at least 200 persons shall have subscribed in the aggregate for at least $200,000 of insurance and shall have paid in full 1 annual premium in money upon the insurance so subscribed.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 73-2-ch672" path="§17">June 19, 1934, 48 Stat. 1148, ch. 672, ch. III, § 17</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 35-517.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 35-617.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Cross References">Prohibition against assessment companies, see <cite path="§31-4331">§ 31-4331</cite>.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
